        <section id='meeting-1841-07-12'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met at the Basement room of the 2nd
            Baptist church on Monday afternoon <time dateTime="1841-07-12">July 12th, 1841</time>. Present, E. L.
            Magoon, J. B. Jeter, A. Snead, Wm. Sands, James Sizer, Richard C.
            Wortham and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>
            The President being absent E. L. Magoon was chosen President pro
            tempore.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by James B. Taylor</p>
          <p>
            The report of the Committee to prepare By-laws was received
            and the committee were discharged.
          </p>
          <p>
            The By-laws were read article by article and after various
            amendments were adopted as follows.
          </p>
          <h3>By Laws</h3>
          <aside>By Laws</aside>
          <ol style={{ listStyle: "upper-roman" }}>
            <li>
              <h3>Officers of the Board</h3>
              <aside>what officers</aside>
              <p>
                The Officers of the Board shall be a President, a Secretary, and a
                Treasurer. These shall be chosen by ballot. <aside>How chosen</aside>The Secretary and
                Treasurer shall be appointed at each annual meeting of the Board.
                <aside>How often</aside>But vacancies may be supplied at any other meeting.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <h3>The Duties of the Officers</h3>
              <ol>
                <li className="first">
                  <h5>1st of the President</h5>
                  <aside>President's duty.</aside>
                  <p>
                    He shall preside at all meetings of the Board. But in case of
                    his absence a President pro tem shall be appointed. The rules of
                    decorum by which he shall be governed, shall be the same with
                    those usually observed in deliberative assemblies <aside>not to give a casting vote.</aside> (with the
                    exception that in case of a tie vote the President is prohibited
                    by the Charter of <PageNumber num={14} /> College from giving
                    the casting vote).
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li className="second">
                  <h5>Of the Secretary</h5>
                  <aside>Duties of Secretary</aside>
                  <p>
                    He shall keep a book or books in which he shall legibly and
                    faithfully record all the proceedings of the Board, conduct the
                    correspondence of the Board file and safely keep all documents
                    committed to his care, subject at all times to the inspection of
                    the members of the Board, but shall not deliver the same to any
                    other than to an agent authorised by the Board to receive them.
                    The record of the proceedings of each meeting of Trustees shall
                    be signed by the President and countersigned by the Secretary.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>3rd The Treasurer</p>
                  <ol style={{ listStyle: "upper-roman" }}>
                    <aside>Duties of Treasurer</aside>
                    <li>
                      For all monies received by him on account of this Board he
                      shall give a receipt and his receipt shall be deemed valid by
                      this Board,
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      He shall pay no monies until the same shall have been ordered
                      by a vote of the Board.  And his proper vouchers for the
                      payment of the same, shall be in order drawn upon him as
                      Treasurer by the President and countersigned by the Secretary.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      He shall keep a regular account of all monies, stocks, bonds,
                      and other effects in his hands or subject to his control;
                      which shall be balanced at least once a year, of which full
                      statement shall be made at the annual meeting of the Board. He
                      shall also submit a sketch of the state of the finances at the
                      quarterly meetings.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      His Books shall be at all times open to the inspection of the
                      Board, or their committee, and before he enters upon the
                      duties of his office, he must give bond and Security for the
                      faithful performance of its duties in the amount of $5,000
                      which bond <PageNumber num={15} /> approved by the Board,
                      shall be deposited with the Secretary.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li style={{ listStyle: "none" }}>
              <h4>Meetings of the Board</h4>
              <aside>Time of An Meeting <ins>ammended <time dateTime="1845-07-29">July 29./45</time></ins></aside>
              <p>
                The Annual meeting of the Board shall be held on the Tuesday
                succeeding the first Sunday in June in the City of Richmond at which
                a full statement of the condition, wants, and prospects of the
                College shall be made.
              </p>
              <p>
                There shall also be quarterly meetings of the Board on the first
                Tuesday in September,  December, and March; and a meeting may be
                called at any time <aside>quarterly meetings</aside>by the President when he or any two members may
                judge it proper. Due notice of all meetings shall be given in the
                <cite>Religious Herald</cite> or some other newspaper published in
                the city of Richmond.
              </p>
              <h6>Manner of becoming bound by Contract or otherwise.</h6>
              <p>
                The Board can become bound by Contract, Deed, Bond, or other legal
                obligation only in the following manner:
              </p>
              <aside>The Board, how bound by contract.</aside>
              <p>
                1st, The obligation shall originate in a vote of the Board in one of
                its meetings; 2nd, The document or documents requisite in the case
                shall be signed by the President, or the President pro tem, and
                countersigned by the Secretary, with the Seal of this Board affixed
                thereto.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
          <aside>Plan of subscriptions</aside>
          <p>
            The Committee to draft a plan for securing subscriptions for Richmond
            College reported and the Committee were discharged.
          </p>
          <p>
            The plan having been read article by article was adopted as follows.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Committee to whom was assigned the duty of reporting a
            plan for the collection of funds for Richmond College, respectfully
            submit the following:
          </p>
          <p>
            It shall be the object of the Trustees to create two
            distinct funds, the Endowment Fund, and the Building
            <PageNumber num={16} />
            <aside>Endowment Fund</aside>
            . For the Endowment Fund, the Trustees shall aim to collect a permanent
            sum of $75,000 to be vested in productive stocks, or otherwise employed
            in a manner the most profitable to the Institution; but in no case shall
            the sum be diverted from the specific object for which it was
            contributed.
          </p>
          <p>
            For the Building Fund the Trustees shall
            endeavor to collect the sum of $25,000 to be expended in the erection of
            suitable <aside>Building Fund</aside>College edifices and supplying them with necessary furniture
            apparatus, etc. etc.
          </p>
          <p>
            To obtain these amounts the agent of the Trustees shall be
            authorized to solicit bequests and subscriptions, to make public
            collections, and to adopt such other means as to him may appear
            expedient.
          </p>
          <p>
            To encourage the friends of the College to make liberal
            contributions to these funds, the Trustees propose that,
          </p>
          <ol style={{ listStylePosition: "inside" }}>
            <li className="first">
              <aside>Priveleges arising from contributions</aside>
              Any person contributing, or, in any manner securing to the College the
              sum of $10,000 shall be entitled to name a Professorship.
            </li>
            <li className="second">
              Any person contributing or securing to the College the sum of $5,000
              shall have the privilege of designating a student to receive
              instruction in all the regular College classes, free of charge for
              tuition forever.
            </li>
            <li className="third">
              Any person contributing or securing to the College the sum of<aside className="pencil"> + $500. ?</aside> $500
              shall have the privilege of naming a student to receive the regular
              course of Collegiate instruction free of charge for tuition.
            </li>
            <li className="fourth">
              Subscriptions for either of these funds may be made payable in five
              equal annual instalments.
            </li>
            <li className="fifth">
              Any person subscribing to the Endowment Fund the sum of <aside className="pencil"> + $500. ?</aside> $500 or
              upwards may retain the principal by giving satisfactory security and
              paying the interest annually.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <PageNumber num={17} />
          <p>E. L. Magoon was added to the Committee to prepare a common seal.</p>
          <p>On motion adjourned</p>
          <div>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec'y E. L. Magoon, Pres. Pro tem.</div>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College held their quarterly meeting in the
            basement room of the First Baptist Church on Tuesday the 1st of March
            1842.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  R. Ryland, Jessee Snead, James Sizer, E. L. Magoon, R. Reins,
            L. W. Allen, A. Thomas, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by James B. Taylor</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read -</p>
          <p>
            L. W. Allen was appointed a Committee to prepare a bond to be signed by
            the Treasurer.
          </p>
          <p>The Committee to prepare a common seal was continued.</p>
          <p>On motion adjourned</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec'y Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1842-06-07' className='annual'>
          <p>
            <aside>2<sup>d</sup>. Annual Meeting</aside>
            The annual meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held in the
            basement room of the Second Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1842-06-07">
              Tuesday the 7th of June
              1842
            </time>. Present, Robert Ryland, Cumberland George, J. B. Jeter, E. L.
            Magoon, A. M. Poindexter, L. W. Allen, Jessee Snead, R. C. Wortham, A.
            Thomas, James Thomas, J. B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <h5>The President in the Chair</h5>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare a bond to be signed by the Treasurer reported,
            and having failed to discharge their duty, were discharged.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion James Thomas was elected Treasurer of the Board and James B.
            Taylor Secretary.
          </p>
          <aside>Record Book</aside>
          <p>
            Ordered that an account of James B. Taylor for Record and Subscription
            Books amounting to $3.50 be paid.
          </p>
          <p>On motion the Trustees proceeded to fill vacancies <PageNumber num={18} />
            occasioned by the death of Peter Winston, and the removal of Wm. F.
            Broaddus. Whereupon <aside>A Fleet & AJ Crane elected Trustees</aside> Alexander Fleet of King and Queen County and A.J.
            Crane of Richmond were elected.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That a Committee consisting of J.B. Jeter, Jno. B.
            Young, and A.J. Crane be appointed to confer with the Board of Managers
            <aside>Com to attend to conveyance of Columbia property.</aside>of the Virginia Baptist Education Society and make arrangements for the
            conveyance of the Columbia property to this Board of Trustees.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. to report Laws for R. College.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a Committee of three be appointed to report to the
            Board at its next meeting a system of Bye laws to be adopted for the
            government of Richmond College. -- Committee: R. Ryland, E.L. Magoon,
            and A.G. Wortham.
          </p>
          <aside>A.J. Crane to draw up a Treasurer's bond</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That A.J. Crane be appointed to draw up a bond in
            proper form to be executed by the Treasurer and that the President and
            Secretary of the Board be authorized to have the bond signed and judge
            of the sufficiency of the securities.
          </p>
          <aside>R Ryland appointed Agent.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the President, Robert Ryland, be appointed an
            agent to collect funds for Richmond College and that he be allowed a
            compensation of $50 per month.
          </p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec. Ro. Ryland, Pres.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1842-09-06'>
          <p>
            The Quarterly meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held at
            the basement room of the Second Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1842-09-06">Sept. 6th 1842</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present: Elder Henry Keeling, A. Thomas, J.C. Crane, Richard
            Wortham, James Thomas, A.J. Crane, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>
            In the absence of the President, Mr. James C. Crane was elected
            President pro tem.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={19} />
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read.</p>
          <p>
            The committee to confer with the Board of the Virginia Baptist Education
            Society and to arrange for the transfer of the Columbia property to this
            Board were continued.
          </p>
          <p>
            The committee to prepare a bond to be signed by the Treasurer reported
            progress and were continued.
          </p>
          <p>
            The committee to prepare By-laws for the regulation of Richmond College
            not being present, no report was received.
          </p>
          <p>On motion adjourned</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec. Jas. C. Crane, Pr. Pro Tem</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1842-12-06'>
          <p>
            The quarterly meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held on
            the <time dateTime="1842-12-06">6th of Dec. 1842</time>, at the basement room of the Second Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President. James Sizer, L.W. Allen, A. Thomas,
            Richard C. Wortham, Albert Snead, J.B. Jeter, A.J. Crane, A.G. Wortham,
            James Thomas, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>The meeting was opened with prayer by J.B. Jeter</p>
          <p>
            The committee to prepare a seal reported by presenting a device,
            whereupon it was recommitted with instructions to have executed such a
            device as may in their judgment be deemed most desirable.
          </p>
          <aside>Report of Agent Doc No 2.</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the President as collecting agent for the College in which
            he declines receiving any compensation for his services was presented,
            whereupon Resolved that the report be accepted.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={20} />
          <aside>Report on rules See Doc No. 3</aside>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare a system of rules for the government of the
            College reported recommending for the present the rule adopted by the
            Seminary, whereupon the report was accepted and the Committee continued.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare a bond to be signed by the Treasurer reported a
            form. The report was accepted and the committee discharged.
          </p>
          <aside>Jas C Crane appointed Treasurer</aside>
          <p>
            The Treasurer elect declined accepting the appointment, whereupon James
            C. Crane was unanimously chosen Treasurer of the Board.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Committee to attend to the transfer of the Columbia property to this
            Board reported progress. The report was approved and the committee
            continued.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. on instruction</aside>
          <p>
            On motion Resolved that a committee be appointed to report a
            system of instruction. Committee:  J.B. Jeter, A.J. Crane, A.G. Wortham.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion adjourned to meet at this place on Tuesday afternoon the 13th
            inst at 1/2 past 3 o'clock.
          </p>
          <p>Benediction by the President</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec            Ro. Ryland, Pres.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1842-12-13'>
          <header><time dateTime="1842-12-13">Dec. 13th, 1842</time></header>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College according to adjournment met at the
            basement room of the 2nd Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present: Robert Ryland, President.  J.B. Jeter, Albert Snead, James
            Sizer, A.J. Crane, L.W. Allen, A. Thomas, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by L.W. Allen</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read <PageNumber num={21} />
            James Thomas, J.C. Crane, and E.L. Magoon entered and took their seats.
          </p>
          <aside>Report on system of Instruction No 4 —</aside>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare a system of instruction presented their report,
            whereupon on motion it was adopted.  See Doc No. 4.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Trustees proceed on next Tuesday afternoon at
            the 2nd Baptist Church at half past three o'clock to the election of a
            Professor and two Tutors and that due notice be given of the same by the
            Secretary.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee be appointed to prepare and report a
            system of instruction and a plan of operations for the College.
          </p>
          <p>
            Committee: Robert Ryland, J.B. Jeter, A.J. Crane, E.L. Magoon, J.B.
            Taylor, Samuel Taylor.
          </p>
          <aside>Pres & Secy to report annually to Prest. & Direct<sup>s</sup>. of Lit Fund</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee consisting of the President and
            Secretary be appointed to report the condition of the College to the
            President and Directors of the Literary Fund by the first day of Sept.
            in every year according to the terms of the charter.
          </p>
          <p>On motion adjourned</p>
          <p>Benediction by the President</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec            Ro. Ryland, Pres.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1842-12-20'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met according to adjournment on <time dateTime="1842-12-20">
              Tuesday
              afternoon Dec 20th 1842
            </time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present: Robert Ryland, President.  James C. Crane, Albert Snead, A.J.
            Crane, A. Thomas, L.W. Allen, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by James B. Taylor</p>
          <PageNumber num={22} />
          <p>
            On motion the Trustees proceeded to elect by ballot a Professor of
            ancient languages and two tutors which resulted as follows:
          </p>
          <aside>Teacher chosen</aside>
          <dl>
            <dt>Robert Ryland</dt>
            <dd>Professor of Ancient Language</dd>
            <dt>Charles L. Cocke</dt>
            <dd>1st Tutor</dd>
            <dt>Samuel C. Clopton</dt>
            <dd>2nd Tutor</dd>
          </dl>
          <aside>Salary of Teachers</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a salary of $900 per annum be allowed to the
            Professor of Ancient Languages, $600 to the 1st Tutor, and $500 to the
            2nd Tutor.
          </p>
          <aside>C L Cocke appointed Steward —</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Charles L. Cocke be appointed Steward of the
            College the ensuing year.
          </p>
          <aside>Terms of board & tuition</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the tuition fee of the College be $35, and that
            the sum of $80 be required for board and $5 for room rent, one half to
            be paid in advance and the balance at the close of the term.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned with benediction by the President</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-03-07'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College held their regular quarterly meeting at
            the 2nd Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1843-03-07">Tuesday the 7th of March 1843</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, Robert Ryland, President.  J.B. Jeter, Albert Snead, J.C.
            Crane, Jessee Snead, Richard Reins, A.J. Crane, E.L. Magoon, and James
            B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by J.B. Jeter</p>
          <aside>com. of instruction</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the committee to prepare and report a system of
            instruction and a plan of operations for the College was received.
            Whereupon the report was recommitted, and Albert Snead was added to the
            committee.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. of conveyance of Columbia</aside>
          <p>The report of the committee to confer with the <PageNumber num={23} /> Board of the Virginia Baptist Education Society and arrange for the
            conveyance of the Columbia property was presented; report accepted, and
            committee continued.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee be appointed to recommend an agent to
            collect funds for the College, at a commission not exceeding 15 per cent
            on funds collected by him.
          </p>
          <p>Committee:  J.B. Jeter.</p>
          <aside>Treasurers securities</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That this Board will approve of a Bond executed by
            James C. Crane, as Treasurer of Richmond College, with the names of
            Jeremiah B. Jeter and Robert Ryland as security.
          </p>
          <p>James C. Crane was allowed to retire.</p>
          <aside>Com. on College Seal</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the President of the Board be added to the
            committee to procure a suitable design to be used as a common seal.
          </p>
          <aside>Com on form of bequests</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That A.J. Crane be appointed a committee to prepare a
            form of bequest in behalf of Richmond College, to be published in the
            <cite>Religious Herald</cite>.
          </p>
          <p>The Board adjourned by benediction</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec            Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-06-06' className='annual'>
          <aside>3<sup>d</sup> Annual Meeting 1843.</aside>
          <p>
            The annual meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held on
            <time dateTime="1843-06-06">Tuesday the 6th of June</time> in the basement of the Second Baptist Church,
            Richmond.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President. Wm. Southwood, A. Fleet, Thomas
            Hume, Richard Reins, J.B. Jeter, E.L. Magoon, James Thomas jun., Jessee
            Snead, Eli Ball, Albert Snead, J.C. Crane, A. Hall, A.G. Wortham, James
            Sizer, John D. McGill, R.C. Wortham, A.J. Crane, James B. Taylor, and
            Joseph Mosby.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by L.H. Alderson</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read.</p>
          <p>On motion the charter of the College was read.</p>
          <p>
            The Trustees proceeded to the annual election of a Treasurer and
            Secretary whereupon: James C. Crane was elected Treasurer and James B.
            Taylor Secretary.
          </p>
          <aside>Report of President no 5</aside>
          <p>
            The quarterly report of the President was received and read. (See File
            No. 5)
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={24} />
          <aside>Seal & Press</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the committee to procure a seal was read. The seal and a
            press to be used with it were presented—report accepted and the bills
            amounting to $25 ordered to be paid.
          </p>
          <aside>Commitee on College Rules</aside>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare rules for the internal regulations of the
            College reported progress and were continued.
          </p>
          <aside>Investment of funds</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Treasurer of Richmond College be required to
            invest any money now in hand or which may come into his hands before the
            next session of the Trustees of Richmond College in the stock of the
            Corporation of Richmond and report thereon at the next meeting.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Committee to secure the transfer of the property belonging to the
            Virginia Baptist Education Society reported progress and were continued.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare a form of bequest reported a form as follows:
          </p>
          <aside>Form of bequest.</aside>
          <blockquote>
            &quot;I hereby give and bequeath to &quot;the Trustees of Richmond
            College&quot; the sum of $___ (or such other property as may be desired
            to devise (if money) to be paid to the Treasurer of the said
            Trustees.&quot;
          </blockquote>
          <p>Report accepted and committee discharged.</p>
          <aside>no agent obtained</aside>
          <p>The Committee to procure an agent reported that no suitable individual had been obtained. Report accepted and the Committe discharged.</p>
          <aside>R. Ryland correspong Agt.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Elder Robert Ryland, President of the Board, be
            appointed a corresponding agent who together with such others as may be
            obtained are hereby appointed voluntary agents of this Board who without
            compensation shall for the present year be authorised to obtain in their
            several vicinities subscriptions and donations for the endowment of
            Richmond College.
          </p>
          <p>The following gentlemen volunteered their services:</p>
          <aside>voluntary agents.</aside>
          <dl>
            <dt>A. Fleet</dt>
            <dd>King William, King and Queen, and Caroline</dd>
            <dt>A. Hall</dt>
            <dd>The Northern Neck</dd>
            <dt>John D. McGill</dt>
            <dd>Essex, Middlesex, and Gloucester</dd>
            <dt>James B. Taylor</dt>
            <dd>Henrico, Hanover, and Goochland</dd>
            <dt><PageNumber num={25} />J.B. Jeter</dt>
            <dd>Chesterfield and Powhatan</dd>
            <dt>J.W.D. Creath</dt>
            <dd>Nottoway, Lunenburg, and Prince Edward</dd>
            <dt>Thomas Hume</dt>
            <dd>Norfolk, Portsmouth, and Norfolk County</dd>
            <dt>Jos. Walker</dt>
            <dd>Hampton, Accomac, and Northampton</dd>
            <dt>Wm. Southwood</dt>
            <dd>Sussex, Greenville, and Southampton</dd>
            <dt>J.R. Scott</dt>
            <dd>Petersburg</dd>
          </dl>
          <p>
            The Committee to prepare a system of instruction not being ready to
            report was continued.
          </p>
          <aside>
            Sec.y to obtain Treasurer's bond.
          </aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Secretary be a committee to obtain the bond of
            the Treasurer duly executed with proper securities.
          </p>
          <aside>Examining Committee</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a Committee be appointed to attend the next
            examination of the College.
          </p>
          <p>Committee: William Southwood, Wm. Carey Crane, J.R. Scott.</p>
          <aside>Resignation of 2nd Tutor Doc No 6.</aside>
          <p>
            A letter from Samuel C. Clopton, the 2nd Tutor, was received resigning
            his place in the College -
          </p>
          <p>Resolved That the resignation of Mr. Clopton be accepted.</p>
          <p>On motion adjourned to meet at the call of the President</p>
          <p>Benediction by the President</p>
          <footer>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec            Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-06-07'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met at the call of the President at the
            2nd Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1843-06-07">Wednesday the 7th of June 1843</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President.  A.J. Crane, Jessee Snead, William
            Southwood, Albert Snead, James Sizer, J.B. Taylor, J.B. Jeter, Jas. C.
            Crane, E.L. Magoon, A.J. Wortham, Richard C. Wortham, Richard Reins, and
            Samuel Hardgrove.
          </p>
          <aside>Mr. Smith appointed 2<sup>nd</sup> Tutor.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Mr. Robert B. Smith be appointed 2nd Tutor to
            supply the vacancy occasioned by the resignation of Mr. Samuel C.
            Clopton at a salary of $500.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That the appointment of voluntary agents be announced
            in the <cite>Religious Herald</cite>.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={26} />
          <aside>French Tutor.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Mr. Guillet be recognized as the Instructor of
            Modern Languages in the College without salary from the Board and
            without being considered a member of the Faculty from the commencement
            of the next term.
          </p>
          <aside>His fee.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Faculty be a Committee to determine the fee to
            be received by Mr. Guillet.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. on premises.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a Committee consisting of the President, A.J.
            Wortham, and A. Snead be appointed to be denominated the Committee on
            the premises to whom shall be referred the duty of directing and
            superintending necessary repairs on the College premises.
          </p>
          <div>On motion adjourned</div>
          <div>Benediction by the President</div>
          <footer>
            <div className='signature'>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div className='signature'>Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-09-05' className='noquorum'>
