        <section id='meeting-1843-09-15'>
          <div><time dateTime="1843-09-15">Sept. 15 1843</time></div>
          <p>
            A called meeting of the Board of Trustees of Richmond College was held
            this day at the 2d Baptist Church, at which were present Ro. Ryland,
            Pres.  J.B. Jeter, E.L. Magoon, A. Snead, J. Snead, R.C. Wortham, A.G.
            Wortham, James Sizer, James Thomas Jr., J.C. Crane, and A.J. Crane =
          </p>
          <p>
            There being a quorum in attendance, the Board proceeded to business and
            A.J. Crane was made sec'y pro tem =
          </p>
          <aside>Funds to be invested.</aside>
          <p>
            J.C. Crane, [indecipherable] Treas. reported that in accordance with the
            resolution of the Board heretofore passed he had invested $400 in the
            stock of the corporation of Richmond =
          </p>
          <aside>Report of Examg. Com.</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the Gent'n appointed by the Board to attend as examiners
            at the last examination of the college was presented and read, and on
            motion it was ordered that it be printed in the <cite>Religious Herald</cite>
            &amp; that it be filed =
          </p>
          <aside>Quarterly Report of Pres. No 8.</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the President was also read, accepted, and ordered to be
            filed =
          </p>
          <aside>Ellyson's Bill</aside>
          <p>
            A Bill of H. Ellyson for printing done was ordered to be paid = amt.
            $3.50
          </p>
          <aside>Treasurer to draw dividends</aside>
          <p>
            On motion it was Resolved that the Treasurer James C. Crane be
            authorised to draw the dividends on the several stocks held by the
            Trustees of Richmond College =
          </p>
          <p>Ro. Ryland, Pres = read the report by Law required <PageNumber num={28} /> to be made annually to the President of the Literary Fund, which was
            approved =
          </p>
          <p>And the Board adjourned =</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">A. Judson Crane, Sec'y pro tem =</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-12-05'>
          <p>
            The regular quarterly meeting of the Board of Trustees of Richmond
            College was held at the basement room of the Second Baptist Church on
            the <time dateTime="1843-12-05">5th of Dec. 1843</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President.  J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball, A.J. Crane,
            James Sizer, L.W. Allen, E.L. Magoon, and J.B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <div>Prayer by Eli Ball</div>
          <p>A. Snead and J.D. McGill appeared and took their seats.</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read.</p>
          <aside>Report of Pres. No. 9.</aside>
          <p>The report of the President was read.  See file no. 9.</p>
          <p>A. Thomas, A.G. Wortham appeared and took their seats.</p>
          <aside>Examg. Comm.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion, Governor McDowell, Mr. Benjamin B. Minor, Dr. Socrates
            Maupin, E.L. Magoon, and Eli Ball were appointed a committee to attend
            the examination of the students at Richmond College to take place on the
            20th of the present month.
          </p>
          <aside>Aug & Sep<sup>t</sup>. vacation months</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the vacation of the College be changed from the
            months of July and August to the months of August and September.
          </p>
          <p>Jas. Thomas, jun., took his seat.</p>
          <aside>Report of Steward No. 10-Bill$201.46</aside>
          <p>
            The communication and an account of 201-46 from the steward were
            presented and read.  See file no. 10.  Account referred to the auditing
            committee.
          </p>
          <aside>Auditing Committee</aside>
          <p>
            On motion, the President, A. Snead, &amp; A.G. Wortham were appointed a
            standing auditing committee.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={29} />
          <aside>Shall the Steward furnish the rooms?</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the committee on the premises be instructed to
            inquire into the expediency of devolving on the steward the
            responsibility of furnishing the rooms at the College for the
            accommodation of the students.
          </p>
          <aside>Tuition fee not to be returned</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a student having paid the money required in
            advance for tuition and leaving the Institution except for sickness or
            some other valid reason shall not be entitled to receive back any
            portion of the sum.
          </p>
          <aside>Shall another teacher of the the juniors be obtained?</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That E.L. Magoon and A.J. Crane be a committee to
            consider the expediency of employing an additional Teacher to take
            charge of the younger students of the College.
          </p>
          <p>The following resolution was introduced:</p>
          <aside>E Ball appointed Agent.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Rev. Eli Ball be appointed an Agent of this body
            to collect funds for endowing the College and erecting suitable
            buildings on the College lot and that he be permitted to collect funds
            for the Virginia Baptist Education Soc. on condition that they shall pay
            one third of his salary.
          </p>
          <aside>salary</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the agent be allowed for his salary the sum of
            $600.
          </p>
          <aside>Refered to a Com.</aside>
          <p>
            After some discussion the resolutions were referred to a committee
            consisting of J.B. Jeter, J.D. McGill, and E.L. Magoon to report at an
            adjourned meeting to be held at this place on Thursday afternoon at 1/2
            past 3 o'clock.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned by benediction</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Sec  </div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-12-07'>
          <p>
            According to adjournment the Trustees of Richmond College met in the
            basement of the 2nd Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1843-12-07">Thursday the 7th of Dec 1843</time>.
          </p>
          <p>Present :  Robert Ryland, President <PageNumber num={30} /> E.L. Magoon, L.W. Allen, James Sizer, J.B. Jeter, A. Thomas, A.G.
            Wortham, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by E.L. Magoon</p>
          <p>
            The committee to whom was referred the resolutions relating to the
            agency reported<aside>Report</aside> &quot;that after carefully considering the question they
            unanmously [sic] recommend the adoption of the resolutions.&quot;
          </p>
          <p>A.J. Crane and A. Snead took their seats.</p>
          <aside>adopted</aside><p>On motion, the report of the committee was unanimously adopted.</p>
          <p>J.D. McGill and James Thomas, jun., appeared and took their seats.</p>
          <aside>Meaning of the Charter.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee be appointed to inquire into the
            proper construction of our charter relative to the appointment of a
            President of the College and report at an adjourned meeting of the
            Trustees.
          </p>
          <p>Committee:  J.B. Jeter, James Thomas, jun., and Jessee Snead.</p>
          <p>
            On motion Resolved That when this Board adjourns, it adjourn to meet
            at this place on next Thursday afternoon at 1/2 past 3 o'clock -
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned with benediction by E.G. Ship</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-12-14'>
          <p>
            The adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held at
            the basement room of the 2nd Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1843-12-14">
              Thursday the 14th of Dec
              1843
            </time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President.  E.L. Magoon, J.B. Jeter, J.B.
            Taylor, James Thomas, jun., A. Snead, A.G. Wortham, and A.J. Crane.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by James B. Taylor</p>
          <PageNumber num={31} />
          <aside>Acceptance of agency by E Ball No 11.</aside>
          <p>
            A communication from Eli Ball announcing his acceptance of the agency
            until June and probably for 12 months without compensation was read -
            whereupon J.B. Jeter and A. Snead were appointed a committee to confer
            with the agent in relation to the best plan of collecting funds for the
            College.
          </p>
          <aside>Meaning of the Charter as to the Pres<sup>t</sup>.</aside>
          <p>
            The committee to inquire into the construction of the charter relating
            to the election of a President reported that after mature consideration
            they are compelled to believe that there has been some informality in
            the former elections of this officer but that this informality does not
            vitiate the proceedings of the Board.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That the report of the committee be accepted and the
            committee discharged.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion adjourned to meet at this place tomorrow afternoon at 1/2 past
            3 o'clock
          </p>
          <p>Benediction by the President</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-12-15'>
          <p>
            The adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held at
            the basement room of the 2nd Baptist Church on the <time dateTime="1843-12-15">15th of Dec 1843</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball, A. Snead, A.J. Crane, E.L. Magoon, L.W.
            Allen, A.G. Wortham, R. Reins, James Thomas, jun., J.C. Crane, and J.B.
            Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Eli Ball was appointed President pro tem</p>
          <p>Prayer by L. W. Allen</p>
          <aside>R. Ryland resigns as the President of the Board</aside>
          <p>
            A communication was read from Robert Ryland vacating his seat as
            president which was ordered to be spread upon the minutes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resolved That the minutes made in Charlottesville on the 8th day
            of June 1841 be so amended as to read <aside>Minutes altered.</aside> &quot;The President of Richmond
            College&quot; instead of &quot;President of the Board of Trustees&quot;.
          </p>
          <p>Upon this resolution the ayes and noes were taken <PageNumber num={32} /><aside>Ayes & Noes</aside> as follows, Ayes, J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball, J.C. Crane, L.W. Allen, R.
            Reins, James Thomas, jun., E.L. Magoon, and James B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Noes, A. Snead, A.G. Wortham and A.J. Crane.</p>
          <aside>R. Ryland's letter of resig. not recorded</aside>
          <p>
            A motion was made to reconsider the vote requiring the letter of Robert
            Ryland to be recorded and carried, the ayes and noes being called for as
            follows:
          </p>
          <aside>Ayes & noes</aside>
          <p>
            Ayes, J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball, J.C. Crane, L.W. Allen, R. Reins, James
            Thomas, jun., E.L. Magoon, and J.B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Noes, A. Snead, A.G. Wortham, and A.J. Crane.</p>
          <p>
            As a substitute for the motion to record the letter of Robert Ryland the
            following preamble and resolution were adopted:
          </p>
          <aside>Letter returned to R. Ryland</aside>
          <p>
            Whereas a letter has been received from R. Ryland vacating his seat as
            presiding officer of the Board under the impression that his election
            was informal and whereas the record of our proceedings appointing him
            has been amended so as to remove the difficulty, therefore Resolved that
            said communication be returned to Mr. Ryland.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned with benediction</p>
          <footer>
            <div className='signature'>Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div>Eli Ball, Pres't pro tem</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1843-12-25'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met at the call of the President at the
            basement room of the 2nd Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1843-12-25">Monday the 25th of Dec 1843</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President, J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball, A. Thomas, A.
            Snead, James Thomas, jun., Edmund Broaddus, R. Reins, Jos. Mosby,
            Alexander Fleet, A.G. Wortham, and J.B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by J.B. Jeter</p>
          <aside>Res of R B Smith no 12.</aside>
          <p>
            A communication was received from Robert B. Smith resigning his place as
            2nd Tutor of Richmond College. Whereupon on motion his resignation was
            accepted.
          </p>
          <p>
            Jessee Snead, J.C. Crane, and A.J. Crane appeared and took their seats.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={33} />
          <aside>Compliment to R.B. Smiath</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Trustees learn with deep regret that the
            health of Mr. Robert B. Smith renders it necessary that he should retire
            from the duties of his office, and they take pleasure in expressing
            their high sense of his intellectual and moral worth.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. to get a successor</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee be appointed to advertise in some one
            of the public papers, and otherwise to inquire for some individual to
            supply the place of 2nd Tutor in Richmond College and to report at an
            adjourned meeting to be held next Monday afternoon.
          </p>
          <p>Committee:  Robert Ryland, Eli Ball, and A.J. Crane.</p>
          <aside>salary.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the sum of $300 be allowed as the salary of the
            2nd Tutor.
          </p>
          <p>The Board adjourned with benediction</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1844-01-01'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met at the 2nd Baptist Church on Monday
            the <time dateTime="1844-01-01">1st of January 1844</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, President. E.L. Magoon, J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball,
            A.J. Crane, A. Thomas, R.C. Wortham, A.G. Wortham, Jessee Snead, and
            J.B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Eli Ball</p>
          <aside>Delegates to College Convention</aside>
          <p>
            A communication having been received from the President of Randolph
            Macon College requesting the appointment of delegates from this Board to
            attend a convention from the chartered colleges of the state to be held
            in this city on the 4th of Jan with the view of obtaining pecuniary
            assistance from the Legislature, It was determined to appoint three
            delegates to attend said convention.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion The President, J.B. Jeter, and E.L. Magoon were
            appointed.
          </p>
          <p>
            James Thomas, A. Snead, and Richard Reins appeared and took their seats.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={34} />
          <aside>Advertise for 2<sup>d.</sup> Tutor</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Committee to inquire for a 2nd Tutor be
            instructed to advertise for some suitable individual to fill this
            office, the appointment to be made on the 20th inst.
          </p>
          <aside>P.Powers elected Prof. Math. & Nat. Philos.y</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Mr. Pike Powers be now appointed Professor of
            Mathematics and Natural Philosophy in Richmond College to enter upon his
            duties the 1st of October, and that he be allowed for his salary the sum
            <aside>Salary $900.</aside>of $900.
          </p>
          <aside>Shall building be erected & board furnished?</aside>
          <p>
            Sundry resolutions relating to the inexpediency of providing board for
            the students of Richmond College, and to the erection of College
            buildings were presented by A.J. Crane and A. Thomas, which on motion
            were referred to a select committee consisting of R. Reins, A.J. Crane,
            and James B. Taylor with the President to report at the next meeting.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned to meet at this place Saturday the 20th inst.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1844-01-20'>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met at the 2nd Baptist Church Saturday
            evening <time dateTime="1844-01-20">Jan. 20th</time>.</p>
          <p>Present:  Robert Ryland, President. J.B. Jeter, Eli
            Ball, E.L. Magoon, A.J. Crane, James Thomas, jun., A.G. Wortham, L.W.
            Allen, and A. Snead.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by E.L. Magoon</p>
          <p>
            The Secretary being absent, Brother Allen was appointed Secretary pro
            tem.
          </p>
          <aside>J.M. Murry 2<sup>d</sup> Tutor.</aside>
          <p>
            Letters from various gentlemen making application for the situation of
            2nd Tutor were read. Whereupon the Board proceeded to the election. Mr.
            John M. Murray of Powhatan was chosen 2nd Tutor of Richmond College.
          </p>
          <p>The select committee concerning the expediency <PageNumber num={35} />
            <aside>Report of Com on buildins, No 14</aside> of erecting College buildings &amp; made a report accompanied with a
            plan of said buildings which was read and laid on the table.
          </p>
          <aside>Southwood's Deed</aside>
          <p>
            A Deed from Elder William Southwood conveying a lot of land in Chicago
            to the Trustees of Richmond College was received and
          </p>
          <aside>Recorded &c.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion The President was appointed a committee to ascertain the
            value of said Lot, to have the Deed recorded and to inquire into the
            propriety of selling it, etc., etc.
          </p>
          <aside>Funds invested</aside>
          <p>
            On motion The Treasurer of Richmond College was directed to invest
            the money now in his hands in the Bonds of the James River and Kanawha
            Company.
          </p>
          <p>On motion adjourned to the next regular Quarterly Meeting</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Sec</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1844-03-05'>
          <p>
            At a meeting of the Board of Trustees of Richmond College held in
            the basement of the Second Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1844-03-05">Tuesday March 5th 1844</time>,
            there were present Ro. Ryland, President., J.B. Jeter, E.L. Magoon, R.C.
            Wortham, R. Reins, James Thomas, jun., A. Snead, and A. Judson Crane =
          </p>
          <p>
            The secretary being absent, A.J. Crane was elected Secretary pro tempore
            =
          </p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read =</p>
          <aside>Com of A Hall no 15</aside>
          <p>
            The President handed in a communication from the Rev. A. Hall addressed
            to him on the subject of his voluntary agency for the Board and the
            bequest of Mr. Grinstead, which was read and ordered to file =
          </p>
          <aside>Powers declines</aside>
          <p>
            A communication was also received and read from Mr. P. Powers declining
            the appointment heretofore conferred on him of Professor in Richmond
            College =
          </p>
          <aside>Freer & D'Wolf's letter</aside>
          <p>
            A communication was read from Freer &amp; D'Wolf
            lawyers of Chicago as a part of the report of the President who was
            appointed a committee to ascertain the value of Lands <PageNumber num={36} />
            <aside>Expenses of Land in Chicago.</aside> in Chicago Ill., which were given to the Trustees of R Col by Rev. Wm
            Southwood - whereupon on motion it was resolved that the Treas'r pay to
            Ro. Ryland the sum of<span style={{ display: 'inline-block', width: 40 }} />expenses incurred by Freer &amp; D'Wolf in
            ascertaining the value of the said Land &amp; recording the deed for the
            same &amp; and for the taxes =
          </p>
          <aside>not to be sold now</aside>
          <p>
            And it was further resolved that the President inform Freer &amp; D'Wolf
            that the Board do not desire at present to sell the said land—and that
            they be desired to advance for the Board the future accruing taxes =
          </p>
          <aside>President's letter</aside>
          <p>
            A communication from the President was read and ordered to file = And on
            motion it was resolved that the enquires propounded therein be addressed
            by the Sec'y to Tutor Cocke with a request that he answer the same =
          </p>
          <aside>Chesterfield R. Road</aside>
          <p>
            It was Resolved that the Treasurer be authorised to represent the stock
            held by the College in the meetings of the Chesterfield Rail Road
            Company =
          </p>
          <p>And thereupon the Board adjourned</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">A. Judson Crane, Sec'y Pro tem </div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1844-06-04' className='annual'>
          <aside>4th An. Meeting</aside>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College held their 4th annual meeting at the
            2nd Baptist Church on <time dateTime="1844-06-04">Tuesday June 4th 1844</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Robert Ryland, William Southwood, L.W. Allen, A. Fleet, J.C.
            Crane, James Sizer, R.C. Wortham, J. Snead, James Thomas, jun., A.J.
            Crane, &amp; J.B. Taylor.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by William Southwood</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read.</p>
          <aside>Treasurer's account See File No 20</aside>
          <p>
            The Treasurer presented and read his account, whereupon it was refered
            [sic] for examination to a committee consisting of A. Fleet and James
            Sizer.
          </p>
          <aside>Grinstead's Bond</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of the Treasurer, Res'd that the amount of $160 received of
            Robert Alexander, on account of Mr. Grinstead <PageNumber num={37} />
            Bond be received in satisfaction of the bond, and the bond be
            surrendered.
          </p>
          <aside>Dr. JP & FI Mettanaur's proposal</aside>
          <p>
            A committee consisting of James B. Taylor and A.J. Crane was appointed
            to consider a communication from Drs. J.P. Mettaner and F.I. Mettaner
            proposing to connect a private medical school in Prince Edward County
            with Richmond College for the purpose of obtaining the power of
            confering [sic] degrees and report at the next quarterly meeting.
          </p>
          <aside>reasons of JB Taylor for declining his appointment as Gen Agent.</aside>
          <p>
            A report was made by J.B. Taylor that in consequence of unwillingness on
            the part of the Church of which he is Pastor to relinquish his services,
            he was prevented from the acceptance of the General Agency to which he
            had been appointed by the Board.
          </p>
          <p>Eli Ball appeared and took his seat.</p>
          <aside>Eli Ball declines the Agency to wh he was appointed</aside>
          <p>
            Mr. Ball reported that he had been unable on account of other pressing
            engagements to fulfil the duties of the agency accepted by him in
            December last, and resigned his agency.
          </p>
          <p>
            Reports were received from A. Fleet, J.D. McGill, and William Southwood,
            voluntary agents of the Board.
          </p>
          <p>Thomas Hudgins appeared and took his seat.</p>
          <p>
            On motion Resolved that the Trustees do now proceed to the
            election of a General Agent.
          </p>
          <aside>R. Ryland appointed Genl Agent</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That Robert Ryland, President of Richmond College, be
            appointed general agent of the Board for the collection of funds, he to
            enter on the duties of the office so soon as <aside>Place to be supplied</aside> the Board can engage the
            services of a competent Professor to take charge of the branches of
            instruction now taught by him, it being understood that no change of
            salary shall take place.
          </p>
          <aside>By a Committee</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee be appointed to secure the services of
            a Professor, or two Tutors, to engage in the work of instruction during
            the absence of the President.
          </p>
          <p>Committee:  The President, Eli Ball, and Albert Snead.</p>
          <p>
            The Committee to examine the Treasurer's account reported that they had
            examined the vouchers, and found them correct.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={38} />
          <aside>Funds now invested.</aside>
          <p>The following are the invested funds in the hands of the Treasurer:</p>
