        <PageNumber num={65} />
        <section id='meeting-1846-12-16'>
          <time dateTime="1846-12-16">
            <p>Richmond, December 16th 1846</p>
          </time>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College met this evening, pursuant to
            adjournment, at the missionary room at the First Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Ro. Ryland, Prst.  A. Hall, R. Reins, J.C. Crane, A.G.
            Wortham, James Thomas., Jr., J.B. Jeter, Eli Ball, James C. Spotts,
            Chas. T. Wortham, and Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Rev. A. Hall</p>
          <aside>Agents report.</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the committee on the agents' report was made and
            received.  (See document &quot;M&quot;)
          </p>
          <p>A. Snead offered the following resolution, which was adopted.</p>
          <aside>List of Subscriptions to be furnished.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the agent be and is required &quot;to furnish the
            Secretary with a perfect list of all the bonds, subscriptions, and cash
            payments obtained by him up to the 31st of this month.&quot;
          </p>
          <aside>Record book</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of A. Hall, the Secretary was directed to purchase a
            record-book for the college.
          </p>
          <p>
            J.B. Jeter, of the committee on the agents' salary, made a verbal
            report; whereupon, on the motion of James C. Crane, the following
            resolution was adopted:
          </p>
          <aside>Allen, S.W. appt<sup>d</sup> agent.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That the Rev'd L.W. Allen be appointed agent of the
            Richmond College for the year 1847 at a salary of seven hundred and
            fifty dollars.
          </p>
          <p>On motion, the Trustees adjourned.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1847-03-02'>
          <div>
            Richmond, <time dateTime="1847-03-02"> March 2nd, 1847</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At a quarterly meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College, at the
            Second Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Ro. Ryland, president.  Eli Ball, James Sizer, A.J. Crane, J.
            Snead, L.W. Allen, Richard Reins, A. Snead, J.B. Jeter, James C. Spotts,
            and Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by the Rev. Eli Ball</p>
          <p>
            The proceedings of the last meeting were read and approved. The agent
            furnished the list required, Dec'r 16th, 1846.
          </p>
          <aside>Resignation of Profsr Holmes</aside>
          <p>
            The resignation of Geo. Frederick Holmes, professor of ancient languages
            was read, and accepted to take effect <PageNumber num={66} />
            at the close of the present session of the college.</p>
          <p>
            A.J. Crane offered the following resolution, which was unanimously
            adopted.
          </p>
          <aside>Complimentary resolution to Profsr. Holmes.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That in accepting the resignation of Geo. F. Holmes,
            Esq’r., a professor in Richmond College, this Board feel regret at the
            necessity imposed upon them of relinquishing his services, and they
            hereby express their high sense of his attainments as a scholar, and his
            character as a gentleman, and they tender to him the expression of their
            kindest wishes for his future prosperity.
          </p>
          <aside>Reynolds Elected Trustee</aside>
          <p>
            The Rev. E.L. Magoon having removed to Cincinnati in the State of Ohio,
            and having thereby vacated his seat as a member of this Board, the Board
            then proceeded to elect, by ballot, a Trustee to fill his place, and the
            Rev. J. Lawrence Reynolds was unanimously elected.
          </p>
          <aside>Gratitous Education of young men</aside>
          <p>J.B. Jeter offered the following resolution, which was adopted;</p>
          <p>
            Resolved That the President and General Agent be authorized to
            enter into such arrangements, on behalf of the Trustees, for the
            gratuitous education of young men in view of an appropriation
            contemplated to be made by the Legislature of this State, as they may
            deem expedient.
          </p>
          <p>On motion J.B. Jeter was added to the Committee.</p>
          <aside>S.W. Allen accepts the agency</aside>
          <p>
            S.W. Allen accepted the appointment conferred upon by resolution of the
            Board of the 16<sup>th</sup>of Dec’r of 1846, as agent of Richmond
            College for the year 1847 at a salary of seven hundred and fifty
            dollars.
          </p>
          <aside>Quarterly report.</aside>
          <p>The president made his quarterly report, which was read and filed.</p>
          <aside>Richmond Academy, upon what terms can it be purchased.</aside>
          <p>S.W. Allen offered the following resolution, which was adopted:</p>
          <p>
            Resolved That a committee of three be appointed to confer with
            the proper authorities upon what terms they might be willing to convey
            to the Trustees of Richmond College the buildings of the Richmond
            Academy in the City of Richmond.
          </p>
          <p>
            J. Snead, J.C. Spotts, &amp; A.J. Crane were appointed on the committee.
          </p>
          <p>On motion the Trustees adjourned.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={67} />
        <section id='meeting-1847-06-08' className='annual'>
          <aside>Seventh Annual Meeting</aside>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime="1847-06-08">June 8 1847</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            The Trustees of Richmond College held their annual meeting at the Second
            Baptist Church of Richmond, Va.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Daniel Witt</p>
          <div style={{ display: 'flex' }}>
            Present:
            <ul style={{
              marginTop: 0,
              listStyle: 'none',
              display: 'grid',
              gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 1fr',
              columnGap: 30,
            }}>
              <li>Ro. Ryland, Pres’t.</li>
              <li>A. Thomas,</li>
              <li>A.M. Poindexter,</li>
              <li>A.J. Crane,</li>
              <li>Chas. T. Wortham,</li>
              <li>A.G. Wortham,</li>
              <li>A. Snead,</li>
              <li>James Thomas, Jr.,</li>
              <li>J.B. Jeter,</li>
              <li>J.C. Spotts,</li>
              <li>J.B. Taylor,</li>
              <li>Wm. Sands,</li>
              <li>L.W. Allen,</li>
              <li>J.C. Jordan,</li>
              <li>D. Witt,</li>
              <li>Rich’d Reins,</li>
              <li>Alex. Fleet,</li>
              <li>J. Stegar,</li>
              <li>J. Snead, &amp;</li>
              <li>Thomas Hume.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>
            The Secretary being absent Thomas Hume was appointed Secretary pro tem.
          </p>
          <aside>Treasurer's Report referred</aside>
          <p>
            The Treasurer presented his report which was referred to a committee
            consisting of Alex. Fleet and J.C. Jordan.
          </p>
          <p>
            The annual report of the president was presented, read and ordered to be
            filed.
          </p>
          <aside>Reported to be correct</aside>
          <p>
            The committee to whom was referred the Treasurer’s report, reported that
            the Treasurer’s report was correct, the report of the committee
            accepted, and the committee was discharged; and the Treasurer’s report
            was ordered to be published.
          </p>
          <p>The Secretary appeared and took his seat.</p>
          <aside>A successor to Holmes</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of James Thomas, Jr., it was Resolved     That a Professor be
            appointed, at the salary of $1,000 per annum, to fill the vacancy
            occasioned by the resignation of Prof. Geo. F. Holmes.
          </p>
          <aside>to be advertized for.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of J.B. Jeter the last Tuesday in July next was fixed as the
            day for the election of a professor, and the Secretary was directed to
            give notice of this by publication in the newspapers of the City.
          </p>
          <aside>Agent's Report</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the General Agent was read, received, and ordered to be
            filed.
          </p>
          <aside>Sect. & Treas<sup>r</sup> re-chosen</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of James Thomas, Jr., Thomas J. Evans was elected Secretary
            and James C. Crane Treasurer.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={68} />
          <aside>Treasurer's bond referred.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of A. Fleet, a committee of two was appointed to take of the
            Treasurer the bond required by the charter of the College and to report
            to the Trustees – The pres’t appointed as a committee for that purpose
            James C. Spotts and Chas. T. Wortham., and on motion A.J. Crane was
            added to the committee.
          </p>
          <aside>Rich<sup>d</sup>. Academy referred</aside>
          <p>
            The committee to confer with the Trustees of the Richmond Academy, in
            relation to obtaining a transfer of this property, reported, and the
            report was laid upon the table.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion, the Trustees adjourned to meet again tomorrow evening at this
            place at 4 o’clock.
          </p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1847-06-09'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime="1847-06-09">June 9 1847</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At an adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held,
            pursuant to adjournment, at the Second Baptist Church of Richmond.
          </p>
          <div className='presentListTwoCols'>
            Present,
            <ul>
              <li>J.S. Reynolds,</li>
              <li>J.B. Taylor,</li>
              <li>A. Snead,</li>
              <li>James Thomas, Jr.,</li>
              <li>Chas T. Wortham,</li>
              <li>Thomas Hume,</li>
              <li>S.W. Allen,</li>
              <li>A.G. Wortham,</li>
              <li>Rich’d Reins ,</li>
              <li>Wm. Sands,</li>
              <li>A.M. Poindexter,</li>
              <div>and</div>
              <li>J.B. Jeter,</li>
              <li>Thos. J. Evans,</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>
            The President being absent, J.L. Reynolds was appointed president pro
            tem.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by the Rev. J.B. Taylor</p>
          <p>The proceedings of the last meeting were read and approved.</p>
          <aside>Com. increased</aside>
          <p>
            The following resolution offered by J.B. Jeter was unanimously adopted.
            "Resolved That the committee of three appointed on the 2
            <sup>nd</sup>
            day of March last to confer with the proper authorities upon what terms
            they might be willing to convey to the Trustees of Richmond College the
            building and lot of Richmond <PageNumber num={69} />
            Academy be increased to seven and that they have power to propose terms
            to the said authorities for the transfer of the said Academy building
            and premises."
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion of R. Reins the number of the committee was increased to nine,
            and the following persons were placed on the committee in addition to
            those already appointed.
          </p>
          <div
            style={{
              display: 'flex',
            }}
          >
            <ul
              style={{
                margin: 0,
                listStyle: 'none',
              }}
            >
              <li>J. Snead,</li>
              <li>J.C. Spotts,</li>
              <li>A.J. Crane</li>
              <li>J.B. Jeter,</li>
              <li>J.B. Taylor,</li>
              <li>J.L. Reynolds,</li>
              <li>Thos. J. Evans,</li>
              <li>Jas. Thomas, Jr.</li>
              <li>A. Snead.</li>
            </ul>
            <div className='tripledSize'>{'}'}</div>
            <div className='tripledLineHeight'>Former Committee</div>
          </div>
          <p>On motion the Trustees adjourned.</p>
          <footer className='rightStacked'>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">J.L. Reynolds, Pres. pro tem</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1847-07-27'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime="1847-07-27"> July 27<sup>th</sup>1847 </time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At an adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held at the
            Second Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols">
            <div>Present,</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Ro. Ryland, Pres’t.</li>
              <div />
              <li>James Sizer,</li>
              <li>J.L. Reynolds,</li>
              <li>J.B. Jeter,</li>
              <li>Wm. Sands,</li>
              <li>A. Snead,</li>
              <li>A.J. Crane,</li>
              <li>J.B. Taylor,</li>
              <li>Jas. Thomas,</li>
              <li>J.C. Spotts,</li>
              <li>R. Reins,</li>
              <li>&amp; Thos. J. Evans,</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>Prayer by Rev. J.B. Taylor</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read and approved.</p>
          <aside>Prof. Christian chosen</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of J.L. Reynolds, the Board then proceeded to the election of
            a Professor of Ancient Languages and Mr. Heath Jones Christian was
            elected.
          </p>
          <aside>No union of the College and Academy.</aside>
          <p>J.L. Reynolds offered the following resolution which was adopted,
            Resolved That the terms proposed by the Trustees of Richmond
            Academy to this Board, forbids us to hope for such an union as would be
            satisfactory to both parties, and <PageNumber num={70} />
            that the whole subject be dismissed.</p>
          <aside>Reply.</aside>
          <p>
            2.  That a respectful reply be made by the Committee to the Trustees of
            Richmond Academy, communicating to them the decision of this Board.
          </p>
          <aside>Christian's Salary $1000.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of James Thomas the Secretary was instructed to inform Mr.
            Christian of his election of Professor of Ancient Languages in Richmond
            College, at a salary of one thousand dollars per annum.
          </p>
          <aside>A Steward</aside>
          <p>
            The President was authorized to employ a Steward for the College for the
            next year.
          </p>
          <aside>Accounts.</aside>
          <p>
            Trustees Evans, Reins and Sands were appointed a committee to examine
            the Steward's accounts.
          </p>
          <p>And then the Board adjourned.</p>
          <footer className='rightStacked'>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1847-07-28'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime="1847-07-28">July 28th 1847.</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At a called meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College at the Second
            Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols">
            <div>Present,</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Ro. Ryland, Pres’t.</li>
              <li>A.G. Wortham,</li>
              <li>J.B. Jeter,</li>
              <li>Wm. Sands,</li>
              <li>J.B. Taylor,</li>
              <li>J.L. Reynolds,</li>
              <li>Rich'd Reins,</li>
              <li>A. Snead,</li>
              <li>Jas. Thomas, Jr. ,</li>
              <li>Thos. J. Evans,</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>
            On motion of J.B. Jeter the price of the board of students was raised
            $10 and that the tuition fee in the College classes be raised five
            dollars.
          </p>
          <aside>Correspondence on expulsion</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of J.L. Reynolds, the President was requested to correspond
            with the Presidents of other Colleges, and learn the practice of other
            colleges in relation to the expulsion of students, and the retaining, or
            returning the College fees to the student expelled.
          </p>
          <p>And then the Board adjourned.</p>
          <footer className='rightStacked'>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={71} />
        <section id='meeting-1847-12-07'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime="1847-12-07">Decm'r 7th 1847</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At a regular quarterly meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held
            at the Second Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols">
            <div>Present,</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Ro. Ryland, Pres’t.</li>
              <li>J.S. Reynolds,</li>
              <li>A.G. Wortham,</li>
              <li>James Thomas, Jr.,</li>
              <li>Wm. Sands,</li>
              <li>Chas. T. Wortham,</li>
              <li>James Sizer ,</li>
              <li>A. Thomas,</li>
              <li>A.J. Crane,</li>
              <li>L.W. Allen,</li>
              <li>Thos. J. Evans,</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>Prayer by the Rev. Mr. Reynolds</p>
          <aside>Presidents Report referred</aside>
          <p>
            The quarterly report of the President was read and received, and so much
            thereof as related to the finance of the College was referred to a
            select committee of James Thomas, Jr., L.W. Allen, &amp; Chas. T.
            Wortham.
          </p>
          <p>
            The President submitted several communications from officers of colleges
            in Virginia on the subject of refunding payments made in advance by
            students who are expelled. Whereupon J.L. Reynolds offered the following
            resolution which was adopted.
          </p>
          <aside>Funds forfeited</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved That whenever a student is dismissed by the Faculty for
            the violation of any law of College, the whole amount of money which he
            may have paid in advance shall be forfeited. But should a student be
            honorably dismissed, a proportionate amount of the money paid in advance
            for board shall be refunded.
          </p>
          <aside>board & tuition</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of J.L. Reynolds, the President was instructed to prepare a
            law in regard to the payment of board money and tuition fees in the
            College.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Committee on the Steward's account made a report which was received
            and adopted.
          </p>
          <p>
            James C. Crane and Chas. T. Wortham were appointed a committee to
            examine the books and accounts of the General Agent.
          </p>
          <aside>Agent's accounts referred</aside>
          <p>
            The Rev. Littleberry W. Allen was appointed General Agent until June
            next at a salary of $1000* <ins>* This was ordered to be changed to $750 at a meeting of the Board on
              the 30th May 1848, the reason assigned that it was a mistake of the
              Secretary.</ins> per annum.
          </p>
          <p>And then the Board adjourned.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={72} />
        <section id='meeting-1848-05-30'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime='1848-05-30'>May 30th 1848</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At a called meeting of the Board held in the Mission rooms at the First
            Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols">
            <div>Present,</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Ro. Ryland, Pres’t.</li>
              <li>J.B. Taylor</li>
              <li>J.B. Jeter</li>
              <li>Jas. Thomas, Jr.</li>
              <li>A.G. Wortham </li>
              <li>Chas. T. Wortham</li>
              <li>A. Thomas</li>
              <li>J.L. Reynolds</li>
              <li>Thos. J. Evans</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <aside>Error corrected</aside>
          <p>
            The proceedings of the last meetings were read, and on motion of A.
            Thomas, that part of the proceedings of the 7th of December 1847 which
            states that L.W. Allen was appointed General Agent at a salary of $1000
            per annum was ordered to be corrected so as to read that he was
            appointed General Agent at a salary of $750 per annum.
          </p>
          <p>
            The President stated that it was the desire of Mr. Massie, one of the
            instructors in the College, to leave the College before the expiration
            of the year for which his services were engaged. Whereupon, J.L.
            Reynolds [offered] the following resolution which was adopted. <aside>Tutor Massie excused</aside>
            &quot;Resolved, That the resignation of Mr. Massie be accepted by
            the Board, to take effect so soon as the President of the College may
            obtain a substitute.&quot;
          </p>
          <aside>J.C. Crane resigns</aside>
          <p>
            J.C. Crane tendered his resignation as a Trustee of the College, which
            was laid upon the table.
          </p>
          <aside>His books to be examined</aside>
          <p>
            James Thomas, Jr., and Chas. T. Wortham were appointed a committee to
            audit the accounts &amp;c of Treasurer James C. Crane.
          </p>
          <aside>Printers bills</aside>
          <p>
            Two bills of the <cite>Richmond Enquirer </cite>for printing, one for $3.50
            and the other for $4.25, were presented and ordered to be paid.
          </p>
          <p>And then the Board adjourned.</p>
          <p>Thos. J. Evans, Secy. Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <div style={{ textAlign: 'center' }}>Ric</div>

        <PageNumber num={73} />
        <section id='meeting-1848-06-06' className='annual'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime='1848-06-06'>June 6th 1848</time>
          </div>
          <aside>8th An. Meetg.</aside>
          <p>
            At the annual meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held, pursuant
            to notice, at the Second Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols">
            <div>Present,</div>
            <ul>
              <li>J.B. Taylor</li>
              <li>A. Snead,</li>
              <li>J.L. Reynolds,</li>
              <li>L.W. Allen,</li>
              <li>Addison Hall,</li>
              <li>Eli Ball,</li>
              <li>Jas. C. Spotts,</li>
              <li>A. Thomas,</li>
              <li>Jas. Thomas, Jr.</li>
              <li>A.G. Wortham,</li>
              <li>Thos. J. Evans,</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>
            The President being absent, J.B. Taylor was called to the chair. Prayer
            by the Rev. E. Ball.
          </p>
          <aside>Presidents Report</aside>
          <p>
            The annual report of the President was read, received and ordered to be
            filed.
          </p>
          <aside>Tutor to be elected.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of A. Thomas the Secretary was directed to advertize [sic] in
            the newspapers of this City for a Tutor of the academical department of
            the College, to fill the vacancy occasioned by the resignation of Mr.
            N.H. Massie, and that the election will take place at the quarterly
            meeting of the Trustees in September next.
          </p>
          <aside>Cranes resignation considered</aside>
          <p>
            The resignation of James C. Crane as a Trustee of the College, which was
            laid upon the table at the last meeting, was taken up and again laid
            upon the table.
          </p>
          <p>
            The committee on the Treasurer's accounts, not being prepared to report,
            was continued.
          </p>
          <aside>Th. Wallace a trustee.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of James Thomas, Jr., Thomas Wallace was appointed a Trustee
            to fill the vacancy occasioned by the death of Richard H. Toler.
          </p>
          <aside>J.D. McGill resigns<br />Baynham elected</aside>
          <p>
            On motion [of] A. Hall the resignation of J.D. McGill was received, and
            on motion of A.G. Wortham Wm. A. Baynham was appointed a Trustee in the
            place of J.D. McGill.
          </p>
          <aside>Evans re-elected Secy</aside>
          <p>
            The Trustees then went into an Election of a Secretary and Thomas J.
            Evans was reelected.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. on the treasurership</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of James Thomas, Jr., Trustees Evans, Spotts, and A. Thomas
            were appointed a committee to examine into and report the legal power
            and authority vested in our Treasurer, under our Charter, over the
            funds, invested stock and other property of the College, and also to
            nominate a Treasurer.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={74} />
          <aside>Agent's accounts referred.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion, James C. Crane and Chas. T. Wortham were appointed a
            committee to examine the accounts of the Agent, and to report thereupon.
          </p>
          <p>And the Trustees adjourned to meet at this place on Tuesday next.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Jas. B. Taylor, Pres. pro tem</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

