        <PageNumber num={75} />
        <section id='meeting-1848-06-21'>
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1848-06-21">June 21st 1848</time></div>
          <p>
            At an adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held
            pursuant to adjournment, at the Second Baptist Church - present,
          </p>
          <p>
            Ro. Ryland, Pres't.  J.B. Jeter, J.B. Taylor, A. Thomas, James Thomas,
            Jr., A. Snead, Chas. T. Wortham, A.G. Wortham, Rich'd Reins, J.L.
            Reynolds, and Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read and approved.</p>
          <aside>Agents accounts reported on</aside>
          <p>
            The committee on the accounts of the agent reported, the report was
            received and the committee discharged.
          </p>
          <aside>Report on the treasureship.</aside>
          <p>
            The committee appointed to examine into and report upon the legal power
            and authority vested in our Treasurer, under our Charter, over the
            funds, invested stock and other property of the College, submitted a
            report which was adopted and ordered to be filed.
          </p>
          <aside>J.C. Crane's resignation accepted</aside>
          <p>
            The resignation of James C. Crane as a member of the Board and Treasurer
            of the College was taken up and adopted.
          </p>
          <aside>Penalty of Treas. reduced to $500.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of A. Thomas the penalty of the Treasurer's bond was reduced
            from five thousand to five hundred dollars.
          </p>
          <aside>Ed. Wortham Trustee of Treas<sup>r</sup>.</aside>
          <p>
            Edwin Wortham was then appointed Trustee, and elected Treasurer of the
            College, in the place of James C. Crane.
          </p>
          <p>
            Rev. L.W. Allen was then appointed General Agent of the College until
            the first of June next, at a salary of seven hundred and fifty dollars
            per annum.
          </p>
          <aside>Petition of students</aside>
          <p>
            The application of the students to change the end of the present session
            from the 31st to the 21st was referred to the faculty of the
            institution.
          </p>
          <p>
            The <time dateTime="1848-08-04">4th of August</time> was fixed as the day for electing a Tutor in the place
            of N.H. Massie, resigned.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={76} />
        <section id='meeting-1848-08-05' className='noquorum'>
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1848-08-05">August 5th 1848</time></div>
          <aside>no quorum</aside>
          <p>
            An adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held on
            yesterday, at which time there being no quorum present, the Trustees
            adjourned to this day.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present: Ro. Ryland, presd't.  J.L. Reynolds, A.J. Crane, Edwin Wortham,
            James Thomas, Jr., A. Thomas, Wm. Sands, Jessee Snead, and Albert Snead.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Secretary being absent, on motion A. Snead was appointed Secretary
            pro tem.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Rev. J.L. Reynolds.</p>
          <p>
            On motion, the board took up the subject of the election of a Tutor to
            fill the vacancy occasioned by the resignation of Mr. N.H. Massie.
            Letters of recommendation from sundry applicants were read and
            considered.
          </p>
          <p>A.G. Wortham (Trustee) appeared and took his seat.</p>
          <p>Leave of absence was granted to Jessee Snead.</p>
          <aside>T.L. Snead a tutor.</aside>
          <p>
            The board proceeded to ballot and Thomas Lounds Snead was duly elected.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion, Resolved, That Mr. Snead, in addition to the
            discharge of the duties of the station to which he has been elected, be
            appointed Tutor of Modern Languages <aside>also of Modern Languages</aside> with the understanding that he
            receive such compensation for such additional service as may be fixed by
            him with the approbation of the president.
          </p>
          <aside>Th. B. Robertson promoted to professor</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved, That Mr. Thos. B. Robertson be appointed Prof. of
            Mathematics with a salary of six hundred &amp; fifty dollars.
          </p>
          <aside>Session to end <time dateTime="07-15">July 15</time>.</aside>
          <p>
            Resolved, That the session hereafter end on the <time dateTime="07-15">15th of July</time>
            without any recess at Christmas.
          </p>
          <p>On motion adjourned</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">A. Snead, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={77} />
        <section id='meeting-1848-12-05'>
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1848-12-05">December 5th 1848</time></div>
          <p>
            At a called meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College at the Second
            Baptist Church.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present:  Ro. Ryland, Presd't.  A.J. Crane, A.G. Wortham, L.W. Allen,
            James Thomas, Jr., J.B. Taylor, James Sizer, Rich'd Reins, Eli Ball,
            Edwin Wortham, Wm. Sands, J.L. Reynolds, and Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>
            Prayer by Rev. Eli Ball. Minutes of the meeting of the 21st June last
            were read and approved.
          </p>
          <aside>President's Report</aside>
          <p>
            The President then read his report, and so much thereof as relates to
            the change of the mode in paying the salaries of the professors, was
            referred to a committee of five.  Committee appointed, J.B. Taylor, E.
            Wortham, J.L. Reynolds, A. Snead, Eli Ball.
          </p>
          <aside>Debt.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of R. Reins the plan proposed for liquidating the present
            debt, of the College, was referred to the same committee.
          </p>
          <aside>Scholarships.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion of James Thomas, Jr., the subject of establishing
            schollarships [sic] was referred to the same committee.
          </p>
          <aside>Removal ✓</aside>
          <p>
            On motion, T.J. Evans, A.G. Wortham and James Thomas, Jr., were
            appointed a committee, to examine into the propriety and report upon the
            subject of moving the college into the City of Richmond.
          </p>
          <aside>Agents Report</aside>
          <p>
            The General Agent submitted a report, which was received and referred to
            a committee consisting of the Treasurer, and Secretary.
          </p>
          <aside>His resignation</aside>
          <p>
            The General Agent tendered his resignation to take effect on the 1st of
            January 1849, which was received; and he was requested to act as agent
            gratuitously.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion, J.B. Taylor, Wm. Sands and James Sizer were appointed a
            Committee to recommend an agent.
          </p>
          <p>On motion, adjourned</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

