          <p>
            At a quarterly meeting of the Trustees of the College, held at the 2d
            Bap. Church in the City of Richmond
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, Ro. Ryland, prst., J.B. Taylor, E. Wortham, L.W. Allen, J.
            Sizer, A.J. Crane, A. Snead, Wm. Sands, James Thomas, Jr., and Thos. J.
            Evans.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by the Rev. J.B. Taylor.</p>
          <p>Minutes read, corrected and approved.</p>
          <aside>President's Report</aside>
          <p>The President's quarterly report was read &amp; received.</p>
          <aside>Finance.</aside>
          <p>The committee on Finance reported and their report was recommitted.</p>
          <aside>Boundary line.</aside>
          <p>
            On motion, the President, Secretary, and A.J. Crane were appointed a
            committee to examine into and report upon the controversy with Mr.
            Rutherford about the boundary line, mentioned in the President's report.
          </p>
          <aside>Chesterfield R.R. Stock.</aside>
          <p>
            The Treasurer was appointed proxy to represent the board in a meeting of
            the stockholders of the Chesterfield Rail Road Company.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned to meet next Tuesday night</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <ins>
          <p>
            Note:  I take leave to add that the two diplomas awarded to P.S. Henson
            &amp; Josiah Ryland were not bestowed until Sept of that year, when the
            first commencement was held at the 2d. Bap. Church. To [sic] many
            students left from the fear of cholera that the session was virtually
            closed without the consent of the Trustees &amp; the Faculty fixed on
            Sept. for the commencements.
          </p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">R. Ryland, Jan 26, '90</div>
          </footer>
        </ins>

