        <section id='meeting-1850-01-21'>
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1850-01-21">January 21st, 1850</time></div>
          <p>
            At a meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College at the 1st Baptist
            Church.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, James B. Taylor, James Sizer, Rich'd Reins, Edwin Wortham, L.W.
            Allen, A.J. Crane, &amp; C.T. Wortham.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion James Sizer was called to the chair in the absence of the
            President.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion, the Secretary being absent, C.T. Wortham was appointed
            secretary pro tem.
          </p>
          <p>
            The committee to examine the finances of the College submitted the
            following report which was adopted.
          </p>
          <div>&quot;To the Trustees of Richmond College,</div>
          <div style={{ textAlign: 'right', marginRight: 20, }}>Gentlemen,</div>
          <aside>Report on Finances</aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              The Committee appointed on the <time dateTime="1849-06-14">14th of June 1849</time> to examine the finances
              of the College since 1846, having submitted a report on the <time dateTime="1849-12-04">
                4th of
                December 1849
              </time> which report was recommitted, have discharged that duty
              and beg leave to report that <PageNumber num={85} /><aside>Receipts</aside>
              the receipts of the College from the <time dateTime="1846-08-01">1st of August 1846</time> to the <time dateTime="1849-08-01">
                1st of
                August 1849
              </time> were
            </span>
            <span className='amount'>$17,164.61</span>
          </p>


          <aside>Payments.</aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              and the payments by the College during the same
              period
            </span>
            <span className='amount' style={{ borderBottom: "1px solid black" }}>$19,191.78</span>
          </p>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">showing a balance against the College on the 1st of August 1849 of</span>
            <span className="amount">$2,027.17</span>
          </p>
          <p>
            For the correctness of the receipts of the College, the committee had to
            rely upon the books and statements of the president, the Rev. Ro.
            Ryland, through whose hands the above sums of money passed.
          </p>
          <aside>Vouchers.</aside>
          <p>
            The payments for the College, by the president, are all supported by
            proper vouchers, except as to the amount of about $20, which from their
            nature could not be receipted for, but which the committee are satisfied
            to be correct and recommend their allowance.
          </p>
          <aside>Balance.</aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              The above balance of $2,027.17 against the College is in favor of the
              Rev. Ro. Ryland, having been paid by him, &amp; the committee therefore
              recommend that the college provide at once for the
              payment of the above sum to him as
              reported
            </span>
            <span className="amount">$2,027.17</span>
          </p>
          <aside>Debt.</aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              which sum is to be increased for salary in 1849
              by
            </span>
            <span className="amount" style={{ borderBottom: "1px solid black" }}>611.91</span>
          </p>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">making the whole amount due him</span>
            <span className="amount">$2,649.08</span>
          </p>
          <p>to be provided for in its payment by the College.</p>
          <div><time dateTime="1849-12-11">Decm'r. 11th, 1849</time> Respectfully submitted,</div>
          <div style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>
            <div>Edwin Wortham</div>
            <div>Thos. J. Evans</div>
          </div>
          <aside>Bond</aside>
          <p>
            On motion the president pro tem James Sizer and the Secretary Thos. J.
            Evans, be instructed to execute the bond of the College to the said Rev.
            Ro. Ryland for the above sum of $2,649.08 to carry interest from the <time dateTime="1850-01-01">
              1st
              day of January 1850
            </time>.
          </p>
          <aside>Report on agents acts</aside>
          <p>
            The committee to examine the accounts of the late agent, the Rev. L.W.
            Allen, submitted the following report which was adopted.
          </p>
          <p>&quot;To the Trustees of Richmond College,</p>
          <div style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Gentlemen,</div>
          <p>
            The Committee appointed to examine the accounts of the late agent, the
            Rev. L.W. Allen, beg leave to submit the following report.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={86} />
          <aside>Agents collections</aside>
          <p className='amountRight'>
            <span>
              We find that the agent collected from the 1st of Janry. 1848 to the 1st
              of June 1849 the sum of
            </span>
            <span className="amount">$1,897.05</span>
          </p>
          <p className='amountRight'>
            <span>Since June 1849 the sum of</span>
            <span className='amount' style={{ borderBottom: "1px solid black" }}>271.50</span>
          </p>
          <p className='amountRight'>
            <span>making the total collections by him</span>
            <span className="amount">$2,168.55</span>
          </p>
          <p>and that he paid</p>
          <table>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
