        <PageNumber num={87} />
        <section id='meeting-1850-06-28'>
          <div>
            Richmond <time dateTime="1850-06-28">June 28th, 1850</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            At an adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held at the
            Second Baptist Church
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, Ro. Ryland, prest.  Edwin Wortham, James Thomas Jr., Wm. Sands,
            Richard Reins, A.G. Wortham, A. Thomas, Chas. T. Wortham, James Sizer,
            A. Snead, and Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Mr. Sands.</p>
          <p>Minutes of the previous meetings read and approved.</p>
          <aside>Boundary</aside>
          <p>
            The committee to examine into and to report upon the controversy with
            Mr. Rutherford in regard to the boundary line was continued.
          </p>
          <aside>Turner and Puryear resign</aside>
          <p>
            Report of the President and the resignation of L. Turner and B. Puryear
            read.
          </p>
          <aside>Dr. Howell a Trustee</aside>
          <p>
            On motion R.B.C. Howell was appointed a Trustee in the place of J.L.
            Reynolds who has removed.
          </p>
          <aside>H. Keeling's seat vacant & J.S. Walthall a trustee</aside>
          <p>
            H. Keeling's seat was declared vacated by continued absence from the
            meetings of the Board, and Jos. S. Walthall was appointed a Trustee in
            his place.
          </p>
          <aside>E. Kingsford <u>vice</u> W. Ritchie</aside>
          <p>
            Wm. Ritchie's seat was declared vacated by continued absence from the
            meetings of the Board and E. Kingsford was appointed Trustee in his
            place.
          </p>
          <aside>J.M. Murray <u>vice</u> J. Mosby</aside>
          <p>
            Jos. Mosby's seat was declared vacated by continued absence from the
            meetings of the board and Jno. M. Murray was elected Trustee in his
            place.
          </p>
          <aside>J.B. Young's seat vacant</aside>
          <p>
            John B. Young's seat was declared vacated on account of continued
            absence from the meetings of the board.
          </p>
          <aside>3 graduates</aside>
          <p>
            On motion the degree of A.B. was ordered to be conferred on Wm. A
            Durfey, J.H. Carter and R.C. Dunn.
          </p>
          <p>
            The resignations of Professor Turner and Tutor Puryear were received.
          </p>
          <aside>Com. on Treasr's acts</aside>
          <p>
            James Sizer and T.J. Evans were appointed a committee to examine the
            accounts of the Treasurer for the last year.
          </p>
          <p>
            T.J. Evans was elected Secretary and Edwin Wortham was elected
            Treasurer.
          </p>
          <aside>Math & Nat. Pilosy united</aside>
          <p>
            The following resolution was adopted. Resolved, That the chairs
            of mathematics and the natural sciences be filled hereafter by one
            person or officer whose salary shall be the same as the President's and
            the professor of ancient languages.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={88} />
          <aside>Prof. Turner re-elected</aside>
          <p>
            Mr. L. Turner was elected professor of Mathematics and the Natural
            Sciences.
          </p>
          <aside>Advertized for.</aside>
          <p>
            The professor was instructed to advertize [sic] for a Tutor in the
            academic department, and a professor of Mathematics and the Natural
            Sciences in the event that Mr. Turner should decline the appointment
            just made. The salary of the Tutor to be as seven in the ratio.
          </p>
          <p>
            Adjourned to meet at this place on the 15th of July next at 8 1/4
            o'clock P.M.
          </p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1850-07-22'>
          <p>
            At a called meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held at the
            Second Baptist Church on the <time dateTime="1850-07-22">22nd of July 1850</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, Ro. Ryland, Prest.  Jessee Snead, R.B.C. Howell, James Sizer,
            A. Snead, A. Thomas, James Thomas Jr., Wm. Sands, E. Wortham, Chas.
            Wortham, Jno. M. Murray, and Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Dr. Howell.</p>
          <p>
            Messrs. Howell and Murray, two of the Trustees elected at the last
            meeting of the Board, reported to the Board that they had taken the oath
            required by the act of incorporation.
          </p>
          <aside>Turner accepts.</aside>
          <p>
            A letter from Prof. Turner was read in regard to the new duties imposed
            by the Board upon the professors at its late meeting, which was
            considered by the board as accepting the appointment.
          </p>
          <aside>Prof. Puryear</aside>
          <p>
            The Board then proceeded to elect a teacher to supply the vacancy caused
            by the resignation of Bennet Puryear. The President read communications
            from gentlemen applying for the office, and after some consideration,
            Bennet Puryear was elected with the title of Professor of Experimental
            Sciences, &amp;c.
          </p>
          <aside>Prof. Montague</aside>
          <p>
            P.H. Montague was elected Professor of Modern Languages to be paid from
            the fees of his classes.
          </p>
          <p>On motion the Board adjourned with the benediction.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jno. M. Murray, Secy. pro tem</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={89} />
        <section id='meeting-1850-12-03'>
          <p>
            At a quarterly meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held at the
            Second Baptist Church in the City of Richmond <time dateTime="1850-12-03">December 3rd 1850</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, Ro. Ryland, Prest.  A. Snead, A. Thomas, James Thomas Jr.,
            James Sizer, E. Kingsford, R.B.C. Howell, Jno. M. Murray, Jos. S.
            Walthall, &amp; Thos. J. Evans.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by the Rev. Mr. Cole of Caroline.</p>
          <p>
            Trustees Kingsford and Walthall reported themselves as having qualified
            as such under the charter.
          </p>
          <p>The minutes of the two last meetings were read and approved.</p>
          <aside>Bond for the Treas<sup>r</sup>.</aside>
          <p>
            The Secretary was instructed to prepare a bond to be executed by the
            Treasurer of the College.
          </p>
          <p>
            The committee appointed on the 28th of June last, to examine the
            accounts of the Treasurer for the last year, submitted a report which
            was received and adopted, and is as follows:
          </p>
          <p>&quot;To the Trustees of Richmond College,</p>
          <aside>Report on</aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              The Committee appointed to examine the accounts of Treasurer E. Wortham
              Esq'r. for the last year, report that they have discharged that duty,
              and find that he had on hand in cash on June the 4th 1849
            </span>
            <span className="amount">$12.23</span>
          </p>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              Since then he has received in interest on
              investments
            </span>
            <span className="amount">739.89</span>
          </p>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              In subscriptions and contributions for the
              endowment
            </span>
            <span className="amount">2335.68</span>
          </p>
          <aside>Receipts</aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description" style={{ paddingLeft: '60%', }}>Making</span>
            <span className="amount" style={{ borderTop: '1px solid black', textDecorationLine: 'underline', textDecorationStyle: 'double' }}>$3087.90</span>
          </p>

          <div style={{ marginRight: 60 }}>
            <p className='leadingDots'>
              <span className="description">Of which there has been invested in stock</span>
              <span className="amount">$2015.32</span>
            </p>
            <aside>Disbursements</aside>
            <p className='leadingDots'>
              <span className="description">Payments for Professors' salaries per rec'ts.</span>
              <span className="amount">760.62</span>
            </p>
            <p className='leadingDots'>
              <span className="description">Leaving a cash balance in his hands of</span>
              <span className="amount">311.96</span>
            </p>
            <div style={{ textAlign: 'right', textDecorationLine: 'underline', textDecorationStyle: 'double' }}>$3087.90</div>
          </div>

          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">The amt. of stock &amp;c on hand on the 4th of June 1849 was</span>
            <span className="amount" style={{ borderTop: '1px solid black' }}>$12,370.00</span>
          </p>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              To which must be added the amt. since invested to
              date
            </span>
            <span className="amount">2,000.00</span>
          </p>
          <aside><u>Investments</u></aside>
          <p className='leadingDots'>
            <span className="description">
              Total amt. of stock on hand this 6th of July
              1850
            </span>
            <span className="amount" style={{ textDecorationLine: 'underline', textDecorationStyle: 'double' }}>$14,370.00</span>
          </p>
          <div style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}>Respectfully submitted,</div>
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: "center", justifyContent: 'flex-end' }}>
            <div>
              <div>Thos. J. Evans</div>
              <div>James Sizer</div>
            </div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: '2em', lineHeight: 2 }}>{'}'}</div>
            <div>Committee</div>
          </div>
          <aside>Boundary</aside>
          <p>
            The committee on the boundary line between the land of the College and
            the land of Mr. Rutherford was continued.
          </p>
          <aside>President's Report</aside>
          <p>
            The report of the President was read and received. A motion was made to
            refer the President's report to a <PageNumber num={90} />
            <aside>Special Com.</aside>Special Committee of three. During the pendency of said motion, remarks
            were made by several Trustees touching the general condition of the
            College, and Professor Holmes, formerly professor of ancient languages
            in this College, being present by invitation, was requested to give his
            views on on [sic] the general interest of the institution, which he did.
          </p>
          <p>
            The motion was carried and the following committee was appointed, E.
            Kingsford, R.B.C. Howell, &amp; James Thomas, Jr.
          </p>
          <aside>B. Manly a trustee</aside>
          <p>
            Rev. B. Manly was elected Trustee in the place of Jno. B. Young Esq'r.
            whose seat was declared vacated by continued absence from the meetings
            of the Board.
          </p>
          <p>
            On motion the Secretary was instructed to have 100 copies of the charter
            and bylaws of the College printed.
          </p>
          <p>Adjourned with the benediction. </p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id='meeting-1851-03-04'>
          <p>
            At a meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held at the Second
            Baptist Church in the City of Richmond on the <time dateTime="1851-03-04">4th day of March 1851</time>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Present, Ro. Ryland, prsdt.  A. Hall, J.B. Taylor, Jno. M. Murray, A.J.
            Crane, J.S. Walthall, Jas. Sizer, A.G. Wortham, R.B.C. Howell, E.
            Kingsford, and T.J. Evans. Prayer by the Rev. A. Hall.
          </p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read &amp; approved.</p>
          <p>
            The committee on the boundary line between the College property and Mr.
            Rutherford was continued.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Secretary reported that he had not had printed the charter and
            bylaws.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Special Committee, to whom was submitted the report of the President
            of the 2nd of December 1850, made a report which was adopted.
          </p>
          <p>
            A. Hall offered the following resolution which was laid upon the table.
            Resolved, That it is inexpedient to move the College to the City of
            Richmond.
          </p>
          <p>The president submitted his quarterly report which was received.</p>
          <p>On motion Mr. Wm. Pollard's appointment as agent was revoked.</p>
          <PageNumber num={91} />
          <p>
            On motion the president was authorized to tender to the Rev. A.M.
            Poindexter the agency for the College at a salary of $1200 per annum.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Faculty of the College and A.J. Crane were appointed to prepare a
            form of diploma in Latin.
          </p>
          <p>And then the Board adjourned. --</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Thos. J. Evans, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Pres't.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

