            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>The above is a carefully prepared statement of the Endowment Enterprise.  The aggregate is $64,428.40, to be diminished by the expenses of the Agencies.</p>
          <p style={{ textAlign: "right" }}>Ro. Ryland, Pres.<br/>J.M. Murray, Secty.</p>
          <p>On motion the following Resolutions were adopted:</p>
          <ol type="I">
            <li>Resolved that the President and Secretary be directed to announce the completion of the $60,000.</li>
            <aside>Order to Complete The Involvement</aside>
            <li>Resolved that in addition to the $25,000 still to be raised of the $100,000 in order to complete the Endowment of Richmond College it is desirable to raise $50,000 for building and other purposes.</li>
            <li>Resolved that the Gen. Agent of the College, Rev. A.M. Poindexter, be requested to continue his agency, until the above amount of $75,000 be raised.</li>
            <li>Resolved that pledges and donations be solicited for the sum of $75,000 to be applied at the discretion of the board to either of the above named purposes, except where the donor prefers to designate the object to which it shall be applied.</li>
            <PageNumber num={109} />
            <li>Resolved that the President and Secretary be directed to publish the plan adopted by the Board to day for raising an additional sum $75,000 and urge it upon the favourable consideration of the friends of the College.</li>
            <li>Resolved that the General Agent be directed to deposite [sic] the bonds obtained with the Treasurer, and that the Treasurer be directed to publish in the same papers in which the announce [sic] of the completion of the $60,000 shall be made, that he is prepared to receive payments and that he shall authorize those indebted to the Board of Trustees, to remit funds by mail at the risk of the Board if they preserve good evidence of having mailed them directed to him in Richmond.</li>
          </ol>
          <p>On motion of James Thomas, Jr. it was Resolved that L.R. Spilman, and Robert Ward be respectfully requested to examine &amp; take a list of all the Bonds, Obligations, and Cash obtained by the General Agent of Richmond College, and through other scources [sic], and certify to it, and deposite [sic] the said Certificates and Bonds with Edwin Wortham, Treas'r.</p>
          <aside>Sub. Agent R.H. Bagby</aside>
          <p>The Committee appointed to confer with the Gen. Agent upon the propriety of employing an additional Agent, reported that it was expedient to employ another, and recommended the appointment of Rev. R.H. Bagby, to devote the whole or a part of his time to the agency at a Salary at the reate [sic] of $1000 per annum. The report was received, and the appointment accordingly made.</p>
          <aside>Interest on Bonds</aside>
          <p>The Treasurer &amp; Gen. Agent were authorized to use their discretion in demanding interest upon bonds for a limited time.</p>
          <p>After which the Board Adjourned.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">John M. Murray, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Prest.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={110} />

        <section id="meeting-1852-06-19">
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1852-06-19">June 19th, 1852</time></div>
          <p>At a called meeting of the Board held this afternoon. Present.</p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols" style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>
            <ul>
              <li>R.B.C. Howell</li>
              <li>Dr. A. Snead</li>
              <li>James Thomas, Jr.</li>
              <li>A. Thomas</li>
              <li>Edwin Wortham</li>
              <li>Wm. Sands</li>
              <li>W. Goddin</li>
              <li>T.J. Evans</li>
              <li style={{ gridColumn: "1 / span 2" }}>&amp; J.M. Murray</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>In the the [sic] absence of the President R.B.C. Howell was called to the Chair, and the meeting opened with prayer by Dr. Snead.</p>
          <p>A communication was received from the President tendering his resignation as President of Richmond College, which being considered was laid upon the table to an adjourned meeting to be held on Wednesday afternoon. --</p>
          <p>On motion R.B.C. Howell, James Thomas, Jr., and A. Snead were appointed a committee to confer with the President in regard to his communications, with instructions to inform him that the Board contemplated relieving him from the Boarding Department at the end of the present session, and to urge him to withdraw the same.</p>
          <p>On motion the Board adjourned to meet Wednesday afternoon 5 o'clock.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">John M. Murray, Secty.</div>
            <div className="signature">R.B.C. Howell, Pres. Pro tem</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <section id="meeting-1852-06-23">
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1852-06-23">June 23, 1852</time></div>
          <p>At an adjourned meeting of the Board held this afternoon pursuant to adjournment. Present</p>
          <div className="presentListTwoCols" style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>
            <ul>
              <li>Ro. Ryland</li>
              <li>A. Snead</li>
              <li>James Thomas, Jr.</li>
              <li>B. Manly, Jr.</li>
              <li>Richard Reins</li>
              <li>C.T. Wortham</li>
              <li>Thomas J. Evans</li>
              <li>W. Goddin</li>
              <li style={{ gridColumn: "1 / span 2" }}>J.S. Walthall &amp; J.M. Murray</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>Prayer by Richard Reins</p>
          <p>The minutes of the previous meeting were read and approved.</p>
          <PageNumber num={111} />
          <p>The committee appointed at the last meeting to wait upon the President in regard to his resignation, presented a report accompanied by a letter from the President withdrawing his communication presented at the last meeting resigning the Presidency of the College.</p>
          <aside>Graduates for 1852</aside>
          <p>The following young gentlemen were recommended by the <u>faculty</u> for graduation at the next commencement of the College: A.E. Dickinson, A. Eubank, A.R. Courtney and E.E. Dunnaway.</p>
          <p>On motion a Committee consisting of Wellington Goddin &amp; Richard Reins was appointed to <u>advertise</u> for a Steward to take charge of Boarding Department of the College at the commencement of the next session. The salary of said Steward not to exceed $250.</p>
          <p>On motion the President &amp; Secretary were authorized to have Circulars prepared stating the $60,000 have been secured in the manner proposed, and they were also authorized to have a copy of the same furnished to each subscriber in the city requesting the [sic] them to hand over the instalments [sic] now due to E. Wortham Treasurer of the Board.</p>
          <p>The Board then adjourned.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">J. M. Murray, Secy.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Prest.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

        <PageNumber num={112} />

        <section id="meeting-1852-07-17">
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1852-07-17">July 17th, 1852</time></div>
          <p>At a meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College held at the Second Baptist Church.</p>
          <p>Present. Ro. Ryland, Prest.  Wm. Sands, B. Manly, A.G. Wortham, J.C. Spotts, Jas. Thomas, Jr., W. Goddin, A. Thomas, A. Snead, Richard Reins, A.J. Crane, R.B.C. Howell, &amp; Thos. J. Evans.</p>
          <p style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>Prayer by the President</p>
          <p style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>Thos. J. Evans was elected Secy. pro tem.</p>
          <aside>Annual Commencements</aside>
          <p>A communication from the Faculty was received in which the Trustees were asked to change the annual commencement of the College from the 15th to the 4th of July -- whereupon the following order was made: That the Annual Commencement of the College be changed from the 15th to the 1st of July.</p>
          <aside>Order in regard Boarding Depart.</aside>
          <p>On motion the following order was made, That the rate of Board be not changed, but that hereafter each boarding Student, be required to furnish his own lights and towells [sic] and have his own washing done.</p>
          <p>The President submitted a statement showing the condition of the College in certain particulars, which was received, ordered to be filed and spread upon the record, and is as follows.</p>
          <p>For the purpose of enabling the Board to understand the exact position of the College finances for the last session (from July 15th, 1851 to July 15th, 1852) I have carefully prepared the following statement</p>
          <p style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>Statement</p>
