        <section id="meeting-1857-07-17">
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1857-07-17">July 17th, 1857</time></div>
          <p>An adjourned meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held this afternoon.</p>
          <p>Present Ro. Ryland, Pres., A.M. Poindexter, Jas. Thomas Jr., B. Manly Jr., J.B. Taylor, A. Thomas, J.B. Jeter, Edwin Wortham, J.L. Burrows &amp; J.M. Murray.</p>
          <p>Prayer by Rev. A.M. Poindexter.</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting being read were adopted.</p>
          <p>The business referred to this meeting being the election of Hotel Keepers, the [sic] stated that he had only one application, to present to the Board, accompanied by a letters [sic] of recommendation which being read was laid upon the table for the present.</p>
          <p>Present T.J. Evans.</p>
          <p>On motion the election of Hotel Keepers was laid upon the table for the present, and the subject of rent for the past year was taken up to be considered and determined.
          </p>
          <p>Absent James Thomas Jr.</p>
          <p>On motion of Richard Reins the Rent for the Hotels for the past year was remitted.</p>
          <p>The following Resolution was now offered <aside>Payment Rents Hotels to be Enforced</aside>by A.M. Poindexter and unanimously adopted.</p>
          <p>Resolved that the Trustees will enforce the payment of rents for theHotels for the ensuing year.</p>
          <p>2. That the College Rooms be equally <aside>Rooms to be divided</aside>divided between the hotels, and that no student shall, after having chosen his hotel leave it without it [sic] without also changing his room.</p>
          <aside>J.P. Tyler Hotel Keeper</aside>
          <p>On motion Mr. Jas. P. Tyler was appointed one of the Hotel Keepers for the ensuing year.</p>
          <PageNumber num={199} />
          <p>On motion the election of the second Hotel Keeper was deferred to a meeting to be held this day two weeks.</p>
          <p>The resolutions offered by Rev. J.L. Burrows at the last meeting in relation to the Professors of Greek and Mathematics were now taken up and being amended as follows. Resolved that the President be uthorized and requested to inform Professor Christian that his resignation as Professor would be acceptable to the Trustees, and the yeas and nays being called was adopted by the following vote.</p>
          <p>Yeas    J.B. Taylor Nays    T.J. Evans</p>
