        <section id="meeting-1857-07-24">
          <div>Richmond <time dateTime="1857-07-24">July 24th, 1857</time></div>
          <p>The Trustees of Richmond College met this afternoon at 4 1/2 o'clock, according to adjournment.</p>
          <p>Present. Robert Ryland, President,</p>
          <p>J.L. Burrows Wm. Sands</p>
          <p>B. Manly Jr. Edwin Wortham</p>
          <p>
            T.J. Evans                   J.M. Murray                &amp; J.B.
            Taylor
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Rev. J.B. Taylor.</p>
          <p>The minutes of the last meeting were read and approved.</p>
          <PageNumber num={200} />
          <p>The President laid before the Board communication from <aside>Prof Christian Resigns</aside> Prof. H.J. Christian resigning the Chair of Greek in the College, which was accepted, and on motion the President was requested to advertise for another Professor to fill the vacant Chair, and the first Thursday (the 3thd of September) was appointed the day of election.</p>
          <p>The Committee on Legacies, etc., presented a report, through T.J. Evans, in the case of Miss Virginia Ratcliff, as follows:</p>
          <p>&quot;To the Trustees of Richmond College&quot;</p>
          <p>Gentlemen,</p>
          <p>As a member of the committee appointed to look into and make <aside>Report on Legacies</aside> report upon the bequest made by Virginia Ratcliffe [sic] to Richmond College -- I eg leave to report that the will of Virginia Ratcliffe (a certified copy of which will is herewith returned) was made on the 10th day of April 1849. She died in June 1853. On the 9th of July 1855, the will was proved and admitted to record in the Richmond Hustings Court, and A. Pleasants the Executor named in the will qualified as such on the 9th July 1855.</p>
          <p>By the will she gave the sum of $950 to Richmond College at the death of her sister Eliza Ann Brend -- This sum she said was due to her from Archibald Pleasants and was secured by a deed of trust on his house and lot, in the City of Richmond. Diligent search has been made for that deed and it cannot be found on record. Mr. Pleasants assures me no such deed ever was made.
          </p>
          <p>Eliza Ann Brend is now dead and the College is entitled to the benefit of <PageNumber num={201} /> the bequest under the will, if any such benefit is ever to accrue.</p>
          <p>Mr. Pleasants has put in my hands papers, receipts of J.H. Walthall for board of V.R., and other accounts against V.R., certified to by Eliza Ann Brend showing that the amount due from Archibald Pleasants to V. Ratcliffe in 1849 has been more than paid off -- and that at her death she was actually in debt to A Pleasants. -- There is no doubt in my own mind that this is so and I do not believe that in a suit against A. Pleasants the College could recover anything. <span style={{ float: 'right' }}>Respectfully,</span>
          </p>
          <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between' }}><div>(A copy signed)</div> <div>Thos. J. Evans</div></div>
          <p>On motion the report was received and the committee discharged from any further action in the case.</p>
          <p>The Board now took up the regular business of the meeting the appointment of a tutor for the Academic Department. (Present J.B. Jeter), and the applications and letters of recommendations from 24 candidates being read, proceeded to ballot, and on the first ballot <aside>Reinhart Tutor</aside> Mr. H.W. Reinhart, of Albemarle received 7 votes out of 8 cast, was declared duly elected Tutor, and the President was requested to inform him of the appointment.</p>
          <p>It having been stated to the Board by the request of A.M. Poindexter that it would be impossible for him to serve as <aside>Chairman Committee on Charter</aside> Chairman of the committee, appointed to petition the Legislature to amend the Charter of the College, on motion the President was appointed Chairman in his stead. Now adjourned.
          </p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">Jno. M. Murray, Secretary.</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Prest</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

