        <section id="meeting-1857-09-05">
          <header>Richmond, <time dateTime="1857-09-05"> September 5, 1857</time></header>
          <p>
            The Trustees met this afternoon, agreeable to adjournment. Present Ro.
            Ryland President, Wellington Goddin, Wm. Sands, Jas. Thomas Jr., J.B.
            Jeter, J.B. Taylor, T.J. Evans, Richard Reins, A.G. Wortham, L.R.
            Spilman, A. Thomas, A.J. Crane, C.T. Wortham, A. Snead, J.L. Burrows, B.
            Manly, and J.M. Murray.
          </p>
          <div className='prayer'>Prayer by the President.</div>
          <aside>Greek Professor to be appointed only for 1 year.</aside>
          <p>
            The President stated the object of the meeting to be the election of a
            Professor to fill the chair of Greek in Richmond College. The
            applications and testimonials of the candidates being read, (absent A.G.
            Wortham), before proceeding to ballot, on motion it was resolved that
            the appointment about to be made should be only for the next Collegiate
            year.
          </p>
          <PageNumber num={205} />
          <p>
            On motion the Board now proceeded to ballot, and Mr. Sydney H. Owens  <aside>Prof Owens Elected</aside> was
            declared duly elected on the first ballot, having received 10 votes out
            of 15 cast.
          </p>
          <p>
            The committee appointed at the last meeting to submit some definite plan
            in relation to the appointment of a receiver of monies from the students
            for board, etc., presented their report which was received and laid upon
            the table to be acted upon at the regular quarterly meeting to be held
            Tuesday afternoon the 8th instead.
          </p>
          <p>On motion the board now adjourned.</p>
          <footer>
            <div className="signature">John M. Murray<br />Secretary</div>
            <div className="signature">Ro. Ryland, Prest.</div>
          </footer>
        </section>

