            Monday<time dateTime="1866-08-06"> August 6<sup>th</sup>, 1866</time>
          </div>
          <p>
            A called meeting of the Trustees of Richmond College was held this
            afternoon at the Grace Street Baptist.
          </p>
          <p>Prayer by Mr. Wm. Sands</p>
          <p>
            Present W. Goddin, J.L. Burrows, Wm. Sands, A.G. Wortham, Edwin Wortham,
            Ro. Ryland, A. Snead &amp; J.M. Murray
          </p>
          <p>
            Dr. Burrows presented an amended form of advertisement<aside>Degree A.M</aside> of the College
            which was agreed to.
          </p>
          <p>
            (On motion of Dr. Burrows the Honorary degree of A.M. was conferred on
            Edmund Harrison, Professor(?).)
          </p>
          <p>
            A communication from Messrs.<aside>Ogden Fleetwood Co</aside> Ogden Fleetwood &amp; Co. was read in
            relation to the Chicago property and referred to W. Goddin, to act in
            regard thereto as he thought best for the interest of the College.
          </p>
          <p>The meeting now adjourned.  </p>
          <footer>
